# BankID Configuration
# ======================
# Environment: "test" or "production"
BANKID_ENV=test

# Path to BankID .p12 certificate file
# For TEST: Download from https://www.bankid.com/en/utvecklare/test
# File: FPTestcert4_20230629.p12
BANKID_PFX_PATH=./certs/FPTestcert4_20230629.p12

# Certificate passphrase
# For TEST: qwerty123
# For PRODUCTION: Get from your bank
BANKID_PFX_PASSPHRASE=qwerty123

# Application URLs
# ======================
# Your application's base URL (used for BankID return URL)
NEXTAUTH_URL=http://localhost:3000

# Your public domain (without protocol)
NEXT_PUBLIC_DOMAIN=localhost:3000

# Database Configuration
# ======================
# PostgreSQL connection string (or your preferred database)
# Example: postgresql://user:password@localhost:5432/ava_mc_booking
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:password@localhost:5432/ava_mc_booking

# For Production BankID
# ======================
# When ready for production, you'll need to:
# 1. Get a production certificate from your bank (.p12 file)
# 2. Update these variables:
# BANKID_ENV=production
# BANKID_PFX_PATH=./certs/your_production_cert.p12
# BANKID_PFX_PASSPHRASE=your_production_passphrase
# NEXTAUTH_URL=https://your-domain.se
# NEXT_PUBLIC_DOMAIN=your-domain.se

# Roaring.io Configuration
# ======================
# OAuth credentials for accessing Roaring.io person and company data
# Get your credentials from: https://developer.roaring.io/
# See ROARING_API_SETUP.md for detailed instructions

# For DEVELOPMENT/TESTING (Sandbox):
# 1. Sign up at https://developer.roaring.io/
# 2. Navigate to API Keys section
# 3. Copy your Client ID and Client Secret from the sandbox environment
# 4. Use test data (see ROARING_API_SETUP.md for test personnummer)
# 5. No costs incurred with sandbox data
ROARING_CLIENT_ID=your_sandbox_client_id_here
ROARING_CLIENT_SECRET=your_sandbox_client_secret_here

# Optional: Specify sandbox base URL (if different from production)
# Only uncomment if Roaring.io provides a separate sandbox URL
# ROARING_API_BASE_URL=https://sandbox.roaring.io

# For PRODUCTION:
# 1. Create production OAuth credentials in the developer portal
# 2. Set up billing and purchase credits
# 3. Replace the sandbox credentials above with your production credentials
# ROARING_CLIENT_ID=your_production_client_id_here
# ROARING_CLIENT_SECRET=your_production_client_secret_here
